<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Rape victims and medically necessary abortions account for less than 1% of all abortions.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
I would like to know where you get theese statistics, I find it rather hard to believe that 1% is a correct statistic (assumption?)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The rest are people who had their &quot;choice&quot; when they chose to have sex, and could have used a condom/pill/etc, and now don't want to take responsibility for that choice.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Some of this statement bothers me, catorgorizing the &quot; rest&quot; all as people who have a choice.  I have a friend, she took the Depo Prevara*sp?* shot as a method of birth control, and 2 months later she came up pregnant. She wanted to have the kid anyway, but the Dr. told her that because of the Depo shot, there could be many possible complications with the pregnancy and actually advised her to have an abortion.<br>
She and her husband took 2 weeks to discuss it and opted to abort.   Catorgorizing all women who have a &quot; choice &quot;  as sluts or an easy lay is wrong...<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Dead is never better than alive. Give the kid a chance, put it up for adoption if you don't want it. And don't tell me it isn't a baby - legal precedents show you can be convicted of two murders if you kill a pregnant woman, so that gives an unborn child some legal status right there. Let's do some simple logic here...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Do you have any clue what a child as a ward of the state goes through?  I draw from personal experiance here as both my parents died when I was pretty young. No other family members wanted to take in a 9 yr old girl, so I was tossed from group homes, to shelters, to foster homes, and even called  the streets of Seattle's &quot; Ave&quot;  home, for about 7 months at the age `13.  Now I know you all could give a damn about my personal experiance here.  But the point I am trying to make is this; I would not wish a life like that on anyone. Especially an infant baby who can not defend themselves, nor oppose any choice made for them.<br>
Not all cases turn out like mine fortunately, there ARE good homes and good people out there that want to adopt, and the child that finds a family like that is extremely lucky and blessed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>People who argue for abortion just don't make sense to me. And as a professional, degreed woman (and yeah, amazingly, I got two master's degrees while a single parent! My life wasnt ruined by being a pregnant teenager, OMG!) I am supposed to be one of the fanatic feminists who think abortions should be legal at all costs. The problem is, the more I thought about it instead of just buying all the &quot;freedom to choose&quot; jargon that had always been fed to me, the less it made sense to me.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Two masters degrees is definatly an accomplishment to be proud of.  But in your post, I think the sarcasm underlying in the statement, being a single mother that made it ect ect is obvious.  No, you are not supposed to be a fanatic feminist, you are only &quot; supposed &quot; to breathe, die, and pay taxes. <br>
You have a few choices here, to be proud of yourself in a mature civil way. Or, you could be boisterous and sarcastic about them, trying to make yourself feel bigger and better than those who's opinions differ from your own.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Flame away, I haven't gotten flamed in a while on here, so I figured I might as well start something - but yeah, unlike some of my usual BS trying to start something, these are my actual opinions on the subject<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
My opinions posted above as well.  Cheers!<br>
